Author: iampieman
Text: I think they tested all that. They don’t have my pee test back yet but it’s probably all good. It makes me think maybe I’ve been imagining my light headedness and fatigue? Like if my body is all okay, why would I have that? Everyone keeps saying I won’t be getting enough vitamins on my very low calorie diet...but if my bloods okay, I must be?   Anyway, I hope things get better for you too.

Author: painxiety
Text: can relate. just had a cbc/cmp come back clean minus hypercalcemia. which is one of the markers they are using on diagnosing me with primary ovarian insufficiency. my dumb ass starved so damn long that i basically get to reach menopause before age 30. dont forget to have them check thyroid and FSH levels (they have to do this like 2, a month apart) to see if its anything hormonal. and if it is... i am really sorry. same boat.
